LocalStorage: stores data as strings, so if need to save objects, have to use use JSON.stringify(object).
    

        .json() method converts JSON object into JS object to use.


const user = {
  name: "Mandy",
  age: 23,
};

localStorage.setItem("user-info", JSON.stringify(user));

localStorage.getItem("user-info"); --> will return a JSON string afterwards, so must parse into object.


JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('user-info')); --> Converts JSON string to JS object.